We are working on
this video workshop.

00:40:33.180 --> 00:40:34.960
And we're going to
get a rough edit soon.

00:40:34.960 --> 00:40:38.320
And that's aimed at HR
folks and executive teams.

00:40:38.320 --> 00:40:43.230
That features Dr.
Akullian and Dr. Wu

00:40:43.230 --> 00:40:45.490
and then me for
like five seconds

00:40:45.490 --> 00:40:48.100
talking about why
this stuff matters

00:40:48.100 --> 00:40:51.740
and why it needs to
matter in your workplace.

00:40:51.740 --> 00:40:53.260
So we accomplished
most of our goals

00:40:53.260 --> 00:40:55.055
or at least getting
partway there.

00:40:55.055 --> 00:40:57.430
It's almost taken a little
while longer than it has been,

00:40:57.430 --> 00:40:59.384
but we're doing OK.

00:40:59.384 --> 00:41:01.800
Now one question sometimes I
get asked is, well why do you

00:41:01.800 --> 00:41:03.720
call it Open Sourcing
Mental Illness?

00:41:03.720 --> 00:41:06.900
And they make some kind of
joke about where's the code.

00:41:06.900 --> 00:41:09.210
And you know, and
it's makes me pissed.

00:41:09.210 --> 00:41:10.470
I don't know.

00:41:10.470 --> 00:41:12.070
Hot button thing--
hot button thing.

00:41:16.660 --> 00:41:19.360
In all my career, last
20 years of my career,

00:41:19.360 --> 00:41:21.842
it's all been based
on open source stuff.

00:41:21.842 --> 00:41:24.300
Not all the things that I've
created have been open source,

00:41:24.300 --> 00:41:25.860
but everything that
I have done has

00:41:25.860 --> 00:41:28.874
been based on open source
technology, every bit of it.

00:41:28.874 --> 00:41:30.540
But I'm going to
assert that open source

00:41:30.540 --> 00:41:32.820
culture and open source
community is not about code.

00:41:32.820 --> 00:41:35.030
That is a mcguffin.

00:41:35.030 --> 00:41:36.440
It's not about the code.

00:41:36.440 --> 00:41:40.280
It's about learning
and sharing together.

00:41:40.280 --> 00:41:42.820
And it's about growing together.

00:41:42.820 --> 00:41:44.330
And it's about
open arms and it's

00:41:44.330 --> 00:41:46.880
about open minds
and an open hand

00:41:46.880 --> 00:41:51.650
to pull the next person up
and help them help themselves.

00:41:51.650 --> 00:41:56.270
It's about a peer group that's
supportive and welcoming

00:41:56.270 --> 00:42:00.340
and embraces each other
to help each other.

00:42:00.340 --> 00:42:02.370
I started this in--

00:42:02.370 --> 00:42:05.160
first time I talked about this
was at an unconference session

00:42:05.160 --> 00:42:11.880
at php tek, which was out
in Roseland in May 16, 2013.

00:42:11.880 --> 00:42:14.225
And I've done about 50
conferences since then.

00:42:14.225 --> 00:42:15.960
I did this little unconf talk.

00:42:15.960 --> 00:42:18.630
And every bit of the success
that we've had turning this

00:42:18.630 --> 00:42:22.650
to a legal entity, fundraising,
the people coming together,

00:42:22.650 --> 00:42:24.900
all of the stuff that we
have done and all the success

00:42:24.900 --> 00:42:28.361
that I've had over the last
three or four years talking

00:42:28.361 --> 00:42:30.360
about this stuff is based
on open source culture

00:42:30.360 --> 00:42:34.140
and it doesn't really have
anything to do with code.

00:42:34.140 --> 00:42:35.812
This is what open
source means to me.

00:42:35.812 --> 00:42:38.145
And that's why I call this
Open Sourcing Mental Illness.

00:42:44.590 --> 00:42:45.460
That's all good.

00:42:45.460 --> 00:42:46.334
That's all fine.

00:42:46.334 --> 00:42:48.250
But I want to get back
to what I kind of think

00:42:48.250 --> 00:42:52.520
is the heart of the
matter and wrap this up.

00:42:52.520 --> 00:42:55.730
At the end of the day, this
is what's going on, I believe.

00:42:58.394 --> 00:43:03.720
It's that our colleagues
and our friends

00:43:03.720 --> 00:43:06.900
and our people, the
people that we work,

00:43:06.900 --> 00:43:09.900
our colleagues, our community
members, the folks that we work

00:43:09.900 --> 00:43:11.520
with in doing this
kind of stuff,

00:43:11.520 --> 00:43:13.650
this sort of tech-oriented
stuff, these tech

00:43:13.650 --> 00:43:18.840
professionals, it's our people,
our friends and our colleagues

00:43:18.840 --> 00:43:26.090
and our people, a lot of
them suffer in silence,

00:43:26.090 --> 00:43:28.510
because they're afraid
to talk about it.

00:43:28.510 --> 00:43:31.250
And sometimes some of
them just disappear on us.

00:43:31.250 --> 00:43:35.530
They go away for one
reason or another,

00:43:35.530 --> 00:43:38.340
and we're left to wonder why
and regret and try to understand

00:43:38.340 --> 00:43:39.494
what happened with them.

00:43:39.494 --> 00:43:41.910
And there's some that we can
save and there's some that we

00:43:41.910 --> 00:43:44.010
can't.

00:43:44.010 --> 00:43:47.340
But the only thing that
allows these people

00:43:47.340 --> 00:43:49.920
to suffer in silence,
and the only reason

00:43:49.920 --> 00:43:52.320
we don't save more of
our kin and our kith

00:43:52.320 --> 00:43:53.760
is because of fear.

00:43:53.760 --> 00:43:55.470
The only reason is fear.

00:43:55.470 --> 00:44:02.236
The only reason that these
people suffer, that we suffer,

00:44:02.236 --> 00:44:07.580
and that we lose many of our
friends is because of fear.

00:44:07.580 --> 00:44:09.440
We have to choose.

00:44:09.440 --> 00:44:13.570
You and I and all
of us have to choose

00:44:13.570 --> 00:44:16.660
to be stronger than that fear.

00:44:16.660 --> 00:44:18.505
We have to choose
to be stronger.

00:44:22.000 --> 00:44:24.120
So thanks for listening.

00:44:24.120 --> 00:44:26.840
I hope you'll consider helping
us out with what we do,

00:44:26.840 --> 00:44:29.690
sharing our message
and resources,

00:44:29.690 --> 00:44:34.270
taking steps to support your
peers, volunteering with us

00:44:34.270 --> 00:44:35.660
if you're interested.

00:44:35.660 --> 00:44:37.540
You can contact us
on our web site.

00:44:37.540 --> 00:44:39.250
If you feel like
donating time or money,

00:44:39.250 --> 00:44:40.810
that is very helpful for us too.

00:44:40.810 --> 00:44:42.930
It is tax deductible.

00:44:42.930 --> 00:44:44.730
So thank you very much.

00:44:44.730 --> 00:44:47.162
I appreciate you giving me
the time to speak on this.

00:44:47.162 --> 00:44:47.870
Thanks very much.

